      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "AI model pricing has changed more in three years than cloud compute pricing changed in a decade. Between 2022 and 2025 the cost of running frontier LLM inference fell 97% for some models, while the introduction of new model tiers added options with 2\u201310\u00d7 the per-token cost of the previous generation. Treating model pricing as a stable input to annual budgets is a material forecasting error. Model price change impact forecasting is the discipline of detecting, assessing, and incorporating price changes into live budget and forecast models \u2014 often within days of a provider announcement."
          }
        ]
      },
