      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 1: Detecting price change events"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Price changes from AI providers are announced via email, changelog pages, and social media \u2014 there is no standardised notification channel. The FinOps team needs a monitoring process that catches announcements reliably and triggers the impact assessment workflow."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Subscribe to provider release notes pages and status pages (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google DeepMind, Mistral) via RSS or email digest."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Monitor official provider social media accounts and engineering blogs for pricing announcements."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set up keyword alerts (e.g., 'pricing', 'token cost', 'model deprecation') on provider changelog pages using a web scraping monitor or a service like ChangeDetection.io."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Maintain a price change log in the FinOps shared drive: date announced, effective date, model ID(s), old price, new price, source URL."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 2: Assessing the affected model portfolio"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A price change for model X is irrelevant if the organisation does not use model X. The first computation is to join the announced price change against the internal model usage log to find the affected workloads and their token volumes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import List, Dict\n\n@dataclass\nclass ModelUsageSnapshot:\n    \"\"\"Monthly token usage summary per model, as of the snapshot date.\"\"\"\n    model_id: str\n    input_tokens: int\n    output_tokens: int\n    cache_read_tokens: int\n    current_input_price_per_1m: float\n    current_output_price_per_1m: float\n    current_cache_price_per_1m: float\n\n    @property\n    def monthly_cost_usd(self) -> float:\n        return (\n            self.input_tokens / 1_000_000 * self.current_input_price_per_1m\n            + self.output_tokens / 1_000_000 * self.current_output_price_per_1m\n            + self.cache_read_tokens / 1_000_000 * self.current_cache_price_per_1m\n        )\n\n@dataclass\nclass PriceChangeEvent:\n    model_id: str\n    new_input_price_per_1m: float\n    new_output_price_per_1m: float\n    new_cache_price_per_1m: float\n    effective_month: int     # months from now\n\ndef find_affected_workloads(\n    usage: List[ModelUsageSnapshot],\n    event: PriceChangeEvent,\n) -> List[ModelUsageSnapshot]:\n    return [u for u in usage if u.model_id == event.model_id]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 3: Computing the cost delta"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once the affected model and its volumes are identified, the cost delta is the difference between what the remaining-period spend would be at the old price and what it will be at the new price."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def compute_cost_delta(\n    snapshot: ModelUsageSnapshot,\n    event: PriceChangeEvent,\n    months_remaining_in_period: int,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Compute the cost delta on the remaining budget period due to a price change.\n    Assumes monthly token volumes stay at the snapshot level (flat projection).\n    \"\"\"\n    old_monthly = snapshot.monthly_cost_usd\n\n    # New monthly cost at changed prices\n    new_monthly = (\n        snapshot.input_tokens / 1_000_000 * event.new_input_price_per_1m\n        + snapshot.output_tokens / 1_000_000 * event.new_output_price_per_1m\n        + snapshot.cache_read_tokens / 1_000_000 * event.new_cache_price_per_1m\n    )\n\n    delta_per_month = new_monthly - old_monthly\n    total_delta = delta_per_month * months_remaining_in_period\n\n    return {\n        \"model_id\": snapshot.model_id,\n        \"old_monthly_usd\": round(old_monthly, 2),\n        \"new_monthly_usd\": round(new_monthly, 2),\n        \"delta_per_month_usd\": round(delta_per_month, 2),\n        \"months_remaining\": months_remaining_in_period,\n        \"total_period_delta_usd\": round(total_delta, 2),\n        \"delta_pct\": round(delta_per_month / old_monthly * 100, 1),\n    }\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For workloads with a compound growth forecast, multiply the delta by the expected growth factor in each remaining month rather than holding volume flat. A 15% MoM growth rate means that the cost saving from a price cut in month N is 15% larger than in month N-1."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 4: Updating the forecast model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The cost delta feeds into the forecast model as a step-change at the event's effective date. The forecast is not re-baselined from scratch \u2014 the growth trajectory and model mix assumptions stay the same, but the rate card is updated."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@dataclass\nclass ForecastModel:\n    monthly_volumes: Dict[str, float]           # model_id \u2192 expected monthly tokens\n    rate_card: Dict[str, ModelUsageSnapshot]    # model_id \u2192 current pricing\n\n    def apply_price_change(self, event: PriceChangeEvent) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Update the rate card in-place at the event effective date.\"\"\"\n        if event.model_id not in self.rate_card:\n            return   # model not in portfolio \u2014 no action needed\n        snap = self.rate_card[event.model_id]\n        snap.current_input_price_per_1m = event.new_input_price_per_1m\n        snap.current_output_price_per_1m = event.new_output_price_per_1m\n        snap.current_cache_price_per_1m = event.new_cache_price_per_1m\n\n    def project_monthly_spend(self, months: int, growth_rate: float = 0.0) -> List[float]:\n        \"\"\"Project total spend across all models for N months.\"\"\"\n        results = []\n        for m in range(1, months + 1):\n            volume_factor = (1 + growth_rate) ** m\n            monthly = sum(\n                self.monthly_volumes.get(mid, 0) * volume_factor\n                / 1_000_000 * snap.current_input_price_per_1m\n                for mid, snap in self.rate_card.items()\n            )\n            results.append(monthly)\n        return results\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Step 5: Determining the action"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The size and direction of the total period delta determines the appropriate action. Not every price change requires a budget revision \u2014 small changes within the forecast tolerance band can be absorbed without escalation."
          }
        ]
      },
